3, \"to\": 1286}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's a vivid example that people are not like atoms that randomly bump into each other.\", \"from\": 1289, \"to\": 1376, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a vivid example\", \"from\": 1294, \"to\": 1309}, {\"ngram\": \"people\", \"from\": 1315, \"to\": 1321}, {\"ngram\": \"atoms\", \"from\": 1335, \"to\": 1340}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We crave and need connection - in a family, local community and a country.\", \"from\": 1377, \"to\": 1451, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"connection\", \"from\": 1395, \"to\": 1405}, {\"ngram\": \"a family\", \"from\": 1411, \"to\": 1419}, {\"ngram\": \"local community\", \"from\": 1421, \"to\": 1436}, {\"ngram\": \"a country\", \"from\": 1441, \"to\": 1450}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Generally, it's good to be proud of your country.\", \"from\": 1453, \"to\": 1502, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"your country\", \"from\": 1489, \"to\": 1501}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Further, the U.S. is a country worth being proud of.\", \"from\": 1503, \"to\": 1555, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the U.S.\", \"from\": 1512, \"to\": 1520}, {\"ngram\": \"a country\", \"from\": 1524, \"to\": 1533}]}, {\"sentence\": \"When victorious U.S. athletes draped the flag over their shoulders, like 400-meter hurdles champion Sydney McLaughlin-Levrone, they beamed.\", \"from\": 1556, \"to\": 1695, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1656, \"end\": 1662, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"score\": 0.9999914236486228, \"rank\": 8.559893266381996e-06, \"text\": \"Sydney\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"When victorious U.S. athletes\", \"from\": 1556, \"to\": 1585}, {\"ngram\": \"the flag\", \"from\": 1593, \"to\": 1601}, {\"ngram\": \"their shoulders\", \"from\": 1607, \"to\": 1622}]}, {\"sentence\": \"What a contrast to the left's push to kneel for the national anthem just a few years ago or smearing the country as systemically racist.\", \"from\": 1697, \"to\": 1833, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"What a contrast\", \"from\": 1697, \"to\": 1712}, {\"ngram\": \"the left's push\", \"from\": 1716, \"to\": 1731}, {\"ngram\": \"the national anthem\", \"from\": 1745, \"to\": 1764}, {\"ngram\": \"the country\", \"from\": 1798, \"to\": 1809}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Olympics are the ultimate competitive stage.\", \"from\": 1835, \"to\": 1883, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The Olympics\", \"from\": 1835, \"to\": 1847}, {\"ngram\": \"the ultimate competitive stage\", \"from\": 1852, \"to\": 1882}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The point is to provide a level playing field and see who comes out on top.\", \"from\": 1884, \"to\": 1959, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The point\", \"from\": 1884, \"to\": 1893}, {\"ngram\": \"a level playing field\", \"from\": 1908, \"to\": 1929}, {\"ngram\": \"top\", \"from\": 1955, \"to\": 1958}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That's equality.\", \"from\": 1960, \"to\": 1976, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"equality\", \"from\": 1967, \"to\": 1975}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The diversity, equity and inclusion crowd does not want that.\", \"from\": 1977, \"to\": 2038, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The diversity\", \"from\": 1977, \"to\": 1990}, {\"ngram\": \"equity\", \"from\": 1992, \"to\": 1998}, {\"ngram\": \"inclusion crowd\", \"from\": 2003, \"to\": 2018}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Equitable treatment means we all end up at the same place,\\\" Democrat presidential nominee and Vice President Kamala Harris has said.\", \"from\": 2040, \"to\": 2173, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2101, \"end\": 2109, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California_Democratic_Party\", \"score\": 0.9964880423007588, \"rank\": 0.0016136712533176129, \"text\": \"Democrat\", \"types\": [\"Q7278\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California_Democratic_Party\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California_Democratic_Party\"}, {\"begin\": 2150, \"end\": 2156, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kamala_Harris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999849933, \"rank\": 1.513128993037566e-11, \"text\": \"Kamala\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kamala_Harris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kamala_Harris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Equitable treatment\", \"from\": 2041, \"to\": 2060}, {\"ngram\": \"the same place\", \"from\": 2084, \"to\": 2098}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Think about how absurd this is.\", \"from\": 2175, \"to\": 2206, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Officials would have to punish Simone Biles for being the greatest female gymnast of all time.\", \"from\": 2207, \"to\": 2301, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2238, \"end\": 2250, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Biles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Simone Biles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Biles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Biles\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Officials\", \"from\": 2207, \"to\": 2216}, {\"ngram\": \"the greatest female gymnast\", \"from\": 2261, \"to\": 2288}, {\"ngram\": \"all time\", \"from\": 2292, \"to\": 2300}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That's the only way to put her in the same place as her peers.\", \"from\": 2302, \"to\": 2364, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the only way\", \"from\": 2309, \"to\": 2321}, {\"ngram\": \"the same place\", \"from\": 2336, \"to\": 2350}, {\"ngram\": \"her peers\", \"from\": 2354, \"to\": 2363}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That would obviously be unfair, but it's analogous to what the left wants the government to do.\", \"from\": 2365, \"to\": 2460, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the left\", \"from\": 2424, \"to\": 2432}, {\"ngram\": \"the government\", \"from\": 2439, \"to\": 2453}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A broader version of this argument would apply that standard to groups.\", \"from\": 2462, \"to\": 2533, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A broader version\", \"from\": 2462, \"to\": 2479}, {\"ngram\": \"this argument\", \"from\": 2483, \"to\": 2496}, {\"ngram\": \"that standard\", \"from\": 2509, \"to\": 2522}, {\"ngram\": \"groups\", \"from\": 2526, \"to\": 2532}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The government, the left would say, needs to give special advantages to certain racial minorities.\", \"from\": 2534, \"to\": 2632, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The government\", \"from\": 2534, \"to\": 2548}, {\"ngram\": \"the left\", \"from\": 2550, \"to\": 2558}, {\"ngram\": \"special advantages\", \"from\": 2584, \"to\": 2602}, {\"ngram\": \"certain racial minorities\", \"from\": 2606, \"to\": 2631}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Think about how this would work at the Olympics.\", \"from\": 2634, \"to\": 2682, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 2669, \"to\": 2681}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The U.S. won 126 medals.\", \"from\": 2683, \"to\": 2707, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The U.S.\", \"from\": 2683, \"to\": 2691}, {\"ngram\": \"126 medals\", \"from\": 2696, \"to\": 2706}]}, {\"sentence\": \"India won just six.\", \"from\": 2708, \"to\": 2727, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2708, \"end\": 2713, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India\", \"score\": 0.9989313122107738, \"rank\": 0.0006132538355746344, \"text\": \"India\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India\"}], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The U.S. population is around 337 million.\", \"from\": 2728, \"to\": 2770, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The U.S. population\", \"from\": 2728, \"to\": 2747}]}, {\"sentence\": \"India's is more than 1.45 billion.\", \"from\": 2771, \"to\": 2805, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2771, \"end\": 2776, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India\", \"score\": 0.9989313122107738, \"rank\": 0.0006132538355746344, \"text\": \"India\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India\"}], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The disproportionate result is obvious.\", \"from\": 2806, \"to\": 2845, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The disproportionate result\", \"from\": 2806, \"to\": 2833}]}, {\"sentence\": \"India has more than four times as many people, but the U.S. won 20 times more medals.\", \"from\": 2846, \"to\": 2931, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2846, \"end\": 2851, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India\", \"score\": 0.9989313122107738, \"rank\": 0.0006132538355746344, \"text\": \"India\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"more than four times as many people\", \"from\": 2856, \"to\": 2891}, {\"ngram\": \"the U.S.\", \"from\": 2897, \"to\": 2905}, {\"ngram\": \"20 times more medals\", \"from\": 2910, \"to\": 2930}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But to even that out would require taking medals away from deserving U.S. athletes.\", \"from\": 2933, \"to\": 3016, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"even that\", \"from\": 2940, \"to\": 2949}, {\"ngram\": \"medals\", \"from\": 2975, \"to\": 2981}, {\"ngram\": \"U.S. athletes\", \"from\": 3002, \"to\": 3015}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Sorry, Noah Lyles.\", \"from\": 3017, \"to\": 3035, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Sure, you won the 100 meters in a literal photo finish, but your country has won too many medals.\", \"from\": 3036, \"to\": 3133, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the 100 meters\", \"from\": 3050, \"to\": 3064}, {\"ngram\": \"a literal photo finish\", \"from\": 3068, \"to\": 3090}, {\"ngram\": \"your country\", \"from\": 3096, \"to\": 3108}, {\"ngram\": \"too many medals\", \"from\": 3117, \"to\": 3132}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Your gold needs to go to someone else.\", \"from\": 3134, \"to\": 3172, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Your gold\", \"from\": 3134, \"to\": 3143}, {\"ngram\": \"someone\", \"from\": 3159, \"to\": 3166}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The injustice would be obvious.\", \"from\": 3173, \"to\": 3204, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The injustice\", \"from\": 3173, \"to\": 3186}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That's analogous to what affirmative action and other DEI initiatives do.\", \"from\": 3205, \"to\": 3278, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"what affirmative action\", \"from\": 3225, \"to\": 3248}, {\"ngram\": \"other DEI initiatives\", \"from\": 3253, \"to\": 3274}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Perhaps that's fine in sports, a leftist might counter, but in real life, the government still needs to step in to help people succeed.\", \"from\": 3280, \"to\": 3415, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"sports\", \"from\": 3303, \"to\": 3309}, {\"ngram\": \"real life\", \"from\": 3343, \"to\": 3352}, {\"ngram\": \"the government\", \"from\": 3354, \"to\": 3368}, {\"ngram\": \"people\", \"from\": 3400, \"to\": 3406}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Here's the problem with that argument: Competition makes you work harder.\", \"from\": 3416, \"to\": 3489, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the problem\", \"from\": 3423, \"to\": 3434}, {\"ngram\": \"that argument\", \"from\": 3440, \"to\": 3453}, {\"ngram\": \"Competition\", \"from\": 3455, \"to\": 3466}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That makes you better, even if you do not come out on top.\", \"from\": 3490, \"to\": 3548, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"top\", \"from\": 3544, \"to\": 3547}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Olympics are a zer